### 1. How to Check Your History and Resume Chats

  #### In the Antigravity CLI (agy)

  • List conversations: You can find all conversation databases and logs stored in your user configuration directories:
      • Database files: ~/.gemini/antigravity-cli/conversations/
      • Chat logs/workspaces: brain
  • Resume a specific conversation: Run the agy command with the --conversation flag and the Conversation ID:
    agy --conversation <CONVERSATION_ID>

  • Continue the most recent conversation: Run:
    agy --continue


  #### In the Antigravity 2.0 Desktop App

  • Type @ in the chat box to trigger the mention menu, then select Previous Conversations to search and view your conversation history or link context directly.
